# Google Sign-In Configuration Template
# Copy this file to app/src/main/res/raw/env and fill in your actual values

# Web Client ID - used for requestIdToken() in Android app and backend verification
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-web-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Google Client Secret - used by backend for additional security
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret

# Android Client ID - for reference (used by Google Play Services to validate app signature)
GOOGLE_ANDROID_CLIENT_ID=your-android-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Instructions:
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console -> Credentials
# 2. Create OAuth 2.0 Client IDs for:
#    - Web application (for GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID)
#    - Android (for GOOGLE_ANDROID_CLIENT_ID)
# 3. For Android client: Add your app's SHA-1 fingerprint and package name
# 4. Copy the actual values and replace the placeholders above
# 5. Never commit this file to version control!
